						<summary>

						<p>Another broken slab in front of the Namaśśivāya-maṭham.</p>						

						<p>Biginning lost. It records the gift of some lands for the worship of gods Ishṭakāmēśvara and Bhairavēśvaradēva and also to certain Mādalachi, daughter of Mahāsāni Dēvaradiyālu (dancer) of the temple. It also refers the signature of Siddhanādani Kaṁnamāḍa. In characters of the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
